ble management: Maps providers to their Reloadable implementations for live configuration updates\n\n- **pkg/services/ssosettings/ssosettingsimpl/metrics.go**: Prometheus metrics for tracking reload failures and other operational metrics.\n\n### Fallback Strategies for Backwards Compatibility:\n\n- **pkg/services/ssosettings/strategies/oauth_strategy.go**: Implements `FallbackStrategy` to load OAuth settings from config files/environment\n- **pkg/services/ssosettings/strategies/ldap_strategy.go**: Implements `FallbackStrategy` for LDAP settings\n- **pkg/services/ssosettings/strategies/saml_strategy.go**: Implements `FallbackStrategy` for SAML settings (when licensed)\n\n### Database Migrations:\n\n- **pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/ssosettings/migrations.go**: Defines the `sso_setting` table migration with columns for id (primary key), provider, settings (JSON), created, updated, and is_deleted timestamps.\n\n## Layer 3: API & Authentication Wiring\n\nThis layer implements the REST API endpoints and wires OAuth connectors to the SSO settings service:\n\n### REST API Endpoints:\n\n- **pkg/services/ssosettings/api/api.go**: Implements the HTTP API with:\n  - `RegisterAPIEndpoints()`: Creates the `/api/v1/sso-settings` route group with four endpoints:\n    - `GET /api/v1/sso-settings`: List all provider settings (requires `ActionSettingsRead`)\n    - `GET /api/v1/sso-settings/:key`: Get settings for a specific provider (requires `ActionSettingsRead` with provider scope)\n    - `PUT /api/v1/sso-settings/:key`: Update provider settings (requires `ActionSettingsWrite` with provider scope)\n    - `DELETE /api/v1/sso-settings/:key`: Delete provider settings (requires `ActionSettingsWrite` with provider scope)\n  - Each endpoint is protected by access control middleware checking specific scopes (e.g., `ScopeSettingsOAuth`)\n  - Responses include ETag-based HTTP caching for efficiency\n\n- **pkg/api/api.go**: Integrates SSO settings API routes into the main Grafana router. 